gomodel:SYNGO_660  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3\nNTT4/RXT-1 localizes to synaptic vesicles in striatal subcellular fractions from rat synaptosomes.\n\nThe pattern of NTT4/RXT-1 immunoreactivity (Western Blot) is similar to the one of the synaptic vesicle protein synaptophysin (Fig 3).\n\nAntibody: purified rb polyclonal anti-Rxt1 (No KO control, but specificity was tested in an earlier study - see link above)\n\nFig.4-8\nTwo procedures were used for immunolabelling: immunoperoxidase and silver-intensified immunogold.\n\nAntibody: purified rb polyclonal anti-Rxt1 (No KO control, but specificity was tested in an earlier study - see link above).\n\n6/6/2017 Pim\n- Protein has TM domains (Uniprot) justifying an \"integral component... \" extension.. Experimental description: FIG. 3. Western blotting detection of Rxt1, RDAT and synaptophysin in rat striatal subcellular fractions. Rat striatal subcellular fractions were prepared...\n\nFig.4-8\nAdult male Sprague-Dawley rats (250 ± 50 g) were deeply anaesthetized by sodium pentobarbital (50 mg/kg, i.p.) and perfused..." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_660" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

